GLOBAL
- Road conditions: posted at city gates and inn boards; update daily; fresh
  reports of raider activity sell well; stale reports get people killed
- Survival basics: water sources in the eastern desert are the Oasis-Pyramid
  Corridor's wells; carry three days' supply minimum; sandstorms move fast
- Saltglass Reach: the overland desert corridor from the pyramid settlements
  to Mafdet; sand-pirate raids are frequent; Sand-Sea Carters' Guild patrols
  but cannot cover the full route; travel in groups
~
GREAT NORTHERN FOREST
- Ancient forest north of Midgaard between the continent and Kowloon delta;
  mythologically attributed to giants' bones (limestone ridges), blood
  (iron-rich springs), and breath (white mists)
- Ashfang warbands and Rootbound cult activity reported; Midgaard road wardens
  track their movements; current intelligence posted at the north gate
- The Lantern Road is the formalized trade artery through the forest; supply
  disruptions here ripple through to Kiess within days
~
FOREST OF CONFUSION
- Lies north of Kiess; formed from a failed druidic quarantine that merged with
  an ancient forest intelligence (the Verdant Depths)
- Mist-fever: psychoactive disorientation with prolonged mist exposure; not
  natural weather; onset can be sudden; symptoms include false memories and
  inability to determine direction
- Kiess Wall Command maintains rope-line corridors and bell-post networks
  through the southern verge; do not enter without a guide or a rope-line
- The Withered Depths deeper in: blight from orphaned Conclave crystal
  experiments in root systems; plant-based creatures in blighted zones are
  aggressive and carry corrupted organic matter on contact
- Verdant Depths at the forest core: distributed living intelligence expressing
  growth, decay, and predation aspects; Heartwood Guardians protect the core;
  no formal contact with city governance
~
EASTERN DESERT
- Oasis-Pyramid Corridor: series of oases and ancient pyramid sites connecting
  the inland desert to Mafdet on the coast; rival excavation camps compete
  for pyramid site access
- Ancient tombs and sealed ruins throughout; many have trap mechanisms that
  still function; some have guardian constructs that do not distinguish
  between excavators and grave robbers because there is no difference
- Scorching Sands / Scorched Wastes: extreme heat zones; travel at night;
  daytime temperatures kill unprotected travelers within hours
- Sand pirates: organized raiding groups that follow caravan schedules; they
  have informants in the departure cities
~
CINDERTEETH MOUNTAINS
- Far northwest; volcanic; do not approach without serious preparation
- Active seismic zones; eruptions produce mineral particulate that is
  toxic to breathe without filtration; the Ashborn are immune
- Abandoned Spirebound Conclave sanctum somewhere in the range; the location
  is disputed; what remains inside is unknown and possibly still active
- Midgaard's Temple of the Resounding Heart runs a seismological watch;
  eruption alerts reach the city via signal relay
~
